definitions.definition: The amount by which something overruns .
examples: At least this year's overrun isn't as unmanageable as last year!

definitions.definition: An area of terrain beyond the end of a runway that is kept flat and unobstructed to allow an aircraft that runs off the end of the runway to stop safely.
examples: The runway has 7,000 feet of paved surface, plus a 2,000-foot grass overrun .

definitions.definition: Air that is whipped into a frozen dessert to make it easier to serve and eat.
